The paper discusses the practical aspects of establishing covert channels in WiFi systems, which involves both security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI) aspects. The paper also discusses the physical layer characteristics of WiFi systems, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The design and implementation aspects of covert channels are also discussed, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves performance analysis of the covert channels, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
